  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I know his guerre-- nom de guerre, Wilk-- 'wolf.' Now, that is a way because the eastern side was very strongly fortified by several bunkers, you know, bunkers, and so on.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So they should try to transfer a majority of [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] partisans on the left flank, you know, and make a diversion attack from the east.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the main attack from the west, where there was only one strong point, you know, from the west.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And not to touch, you know, the-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] no, [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] where the-- where the planes land, you know.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And then it started to-- in-- I learned that, in, in the forest Rudniki and the forest Nacha, one is about 25 kilometers from Vilna to the southwest.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the other, probably some 60 or 70 kilometers-- are Jewish partisans.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But I organized there a group Polish partisans.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And then it was probably in June '42, working, you know, in the hothouse or the hotbeds, you know, over that-- I saw airplanes [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] bombarding the Nacha-- the Nacha Forest here going-- no, they, they came from, from Vilna airfield-- Porubanek-- bombarded Rudniki Forest, flew south, bombarded, bombarded Nacha Forest.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then around it-- and again, you know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There were three planes, taking-- it seems.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "This I much remember.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then a couple days later, one of the officers, whom I put in charge, tells-- comes to me and said, well, I, I had a-- I did a good deed.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I said, what happened?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Oh, he said, you know, day before yesterday, when they bombarded, bombarded Rudniki Forest and the Nacha Forest?",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
